<h2 id="course-notes">Course Notes</h2>

<p>This is an upper level course and students are expected to be extremely self-directed. This is a 3 credit class with 6 hours of outside class work per week.</p>

<h4 id="books-on-course-reserve">Books on Course Reserve</h4>

<p>There are no required books, but there are several books on Raspberry Pi available at the library. There are a ton of websites for learning Raspberry Pi. We will be using Linux family of operating systems in this class. There are an unbelievable amount of books, websites and other (generally free) resources for learning and using Linux. See the resources page for some links.</p>

<p>Books available in the library:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Raspberry Pi cookbook</li>
  <li>Getting Started With Raspberry Pi</li>
</ul>

